summary: This is an email chain from October 22, 2019, regarding the scheduling and subsequent cancellation of a conference call. The call was intended to facilitate a conversation between an Epstein victim and her attorneys, who were located in different places.

events.title: Scheduled Conference Call with Epstein Victim
events.description: A conference call was scheduled for the afternoon of October 22, 2019, to speak with an Epstein victim and her attorneys.

events.title: Cancellation of Conference Call
events.description: The scheduled conference call with the Epstein victim and her attorneys was cancelled on the same day it was to occur.

keyFacts: A conference call was arranged for October 22, 2019, to communicate with an Epstein victim and her legal team.
The call was cancelled on short notice on the same day it was scheduled.
The document indicates ongoing legal communications or preparations involving an Epstein victim in late 2019.
The victim's attorneys were geographically dispersed, requiring a conference call setup.
